// The `prelude.file` sub-module: read a `file` value's content and metadata in-runtime. A `file` is a
// handle into the project's blob store (the value carries the reference; the bytes stay put), so
// programs pass files around for free — these primitives are the bridge for the moments the content
// itself must go on a wire, e.g. base64 for a multimodal model's `inline_data` part.

@"The file's bytes, base64-encoded — the inline shape multimodal model APIs take. The whole content
materialises as one string, so mind the size (a large file makes a large request body)."
primitive agent read_base64(value: file) -> string

@"The file's recorded MIME type (e.g. \"image/png\"), or \"\" when none was recorded at upload."
primitive agent content_type(value: file) -> string

@"The file's size in bytes, read from the handle (no content download)."
primitive agent size(value: file) -> integer
